NFT Lingo and Acronyms

- GM: Good Morning
- WGMI / WAGMI: We're all going to make it
- NGMI: Not gonna make it
- Mint/Minting: Action of recording a new digital asset to the blockchain. For new NFT collections, buyers will "mint" the new NFT and it will become available on secondary markets for resale afterwards. 
- Floor: Cheapest price for a piece in an NFT collection
- PFP: Profile Picture
- FOMO: Fear of Missing Out
- Rug/Rug Pull: Scam Projects
- No cap: No Lie
- 1:1 or 1/1: Art where each piece is unique
- LFG: Let's fucking go!
- OG: Early project finder/adopter
- JPEG/JPG: File format used to store digital images on a computer (most nfts are actually png but people talk about jpeg)
- IYKYK: If you know you know
- DYOR: Do Your Own Research
- Aped/Apeing in: Getting into a project without doing much research / not long after the project launch. Often due to FOMO
- FUD: Fear, Uncertainty, and Doubt. This is used to caused fear among a project so the price can go down.
- Shill: Trying to convince other people to buy something where you hold a position. (You will get shilled all the time in the NFT space. Don't listen to others and DYOR) 
- Burning: Means permanently deleting or eliminating a specific amount of cryptocurrency/NFT assets within a collection. Often done to reduce the supply and increase value for holders. 
- DeFi: Decentralised Finance. 
- Staking: Temporarily lock your NFT into a wallet, so you can't access or spend it. Many NFT projects will rewards holders with tokens / perks if they stake their NFT instead of selling them.
- WL: Whitelist / early access to new collections. 
- Sweeping the floor: Buying a good number of pieces from the lowest price, raising the overall price of the collection. 
- BAYC: Bored Ape Yatch Club (Iconic NFT collection) 
- MAYC: Mutant Ape Yatch Club (second collection from BAYC)
- OS: OpenSea (Largest Ethereum NFT marketplace)
- ME: MagicEden (Solana Blockchain NFT marketplace)

NFT Lingo and Acronyms

- GM: Good Morning
- WGMI / WAGMI: We're all going to make it
- NGMI: Not gonna make it
- Mint/Minting: Action of recording a new digital asset to the blockchain. For new NFT collections, buyers will "mint" the new NFT and it will become available on secondary markets for resale afterwards. 
- Floor: Cheapest price for a piece in an NFT collection
- PFP: Profile Picture
- FOMO: Fear of Missing Out
- Rug/Rug Pull: Scam Projects
- No cap: No Lie
- 1:1 or 1/1: Art where each piece is unique
- LFG: Let's fucking go!
- OG: Early project finder/adopter
- JPEG/JPG: File format used to store digital images on a computer (most nfts are actually png but people talk about jpeg)
- IYKYK: If you know you know
- DYOR: Do Your Own Research
- Aped/Apeing in: Getting into a project without doing much research / not long after the project launch. Often due to FOMO
- FUD: Fear, Uncertainty, and Doubt. This is used to caused fear among a project so the price can go down.
- Shill: Trying to convince other people to buy something where you hold a position. (You will get shilled all the time in the NFT space. Don't listen to others and DYOR) 
- Burning: Means permanently deleting or eliminating a specific amount of cryptocurrency/NFT assets within a collection. Often done to reduce the supply and increase value for holders. 
- DeFi: Decentralised Finance. 
- Staking: Temporarily lock your NFT into a wallet, so you can't access or spend it. Many NFT projects will rewards holders with tokens / perks if they stake their NFT instead of selling them.
- WL: Whitelist / early access to new collections. 
- Sweeping the floor: Buying a good number of pieces from the lowest price, raising the overall price of the collection. 
- BAYC: Bored Ape Yatch Club (Iconic NFT collection) 
- MAYC: Mutant Ape Yatch Club (second collection from BAYC)
- OS: OpenSea (Largest Ethereum NFT marketplace)
- ME: MagicEden (Solana Blockchain NFT marketplace)
